Test with this:

  # ASCII
  $ lpdoc -t ascii markdown_simple.lpdoc
  $ lpdoc --allow_markdown=no -t ascii markup_simple.lpdoc

  # HTML
  $ lpdoc -t html markdown_simple.lpdoc
  $ lpdoc --allow_markdown=no -t html markup_simple.lpdoc

  # PDF
  $ lpdoc -t pdf markdown_simple.lpdoc
  $ lpdoc --allow_markdown=no -t pdf markup_simple.lpdoc

Markdown and syntax highlight are enabled by default in LPdoc. Add
"--syntax_highlight=no" to disable syntax highlight.  highlight.

The output of both markup and markdown versions should be similar (not
equivalent at this moment since the markdown versions contains notes).

